#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:4
msgid "cmake-presets(7)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:7
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:11
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:15
msgid ""
"One problem that CMake users often face is sharing settings with other "
"people for common ways to configure a project. This may be done to support "
"CI builds, or for users who frequently use the same build. CMake supports "
"two main files, ``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json``, that "
"allow users to specify common configure options and share them with others. "
"CMake also supports files included with the ``include`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:22
msgid ""
"``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` live in the project's "
"root directory. They both have exactly the same format, and both are "
"optional (though at least one must be present if :option:`--preset <cmake --"
"preset>` is specified).  ``CMakePresets.json`` is meant to specify project-"
"wide build details, while ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` is meant for developers "
"to specify their own local build details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:29
msgid ""
"``CMakePresets.json`` may be checked into a version control system, and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` should NOT be checked in. For example, if a "
"project is using Git, ``CMakePresets.json`` may be tracked, and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` should be added to the ``.gitignore``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:35
msgid "Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:37
msgid "The files are a JSON document with an object as the root:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:39
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"version\": 10,\n"
"  \"cmakeMinimumRequired\": {\n"
"    \"major\": 3,\n"
"    \"minor\": 23,\n"
"    \"patch\": 0\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"$comment\": \"An example CMakePresets.json file\",\n"
"  \"include\": [\n"
"    \"otherThings.json\",\n"
"    \"moreThings.json\"\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"configurePresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"$comment\": [\n"
"        \"This is a comment row.\",\n"
"        \"This is another comment,\",\n"
"        \"just because we can do it\"\n"
"      ],\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Default Config\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"Default build using Ninja generator\",\n"
"      \"generator\": \"Ninja\",\n"
"      \"binaryDir\": \"${sourceDir}/build/default\",\n"
"      \"cacheVariables\": {\n"
"        \"FIRST_CACHE_VARIABLE\": {\n"
"          \"type\": \"BOOL\",\n"
"          \"value\": \"OFF\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"SECOND_CACHE_VARIABLE\": \"ON\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"environment\": {\n"
"        \"MY_ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLE\": \"Test\",\n"
"        \"PATH\": \"$env{HOME}/ninja/bin:$penv{PATH}\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"vendor\": {\n"
"        \"example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0\": {\n"
"          \"autoFormat\": true\n"
"        }\n"
"      }\n"
"    },\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"ninja-multi\",\n"
"      \"inherits\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Ninja Multi-Config\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"Default build using Ninja Multi-Config "
"generator\",\n"
"      \"generator\": \"Ninja Multi-Config\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"windows-only\",\n"
"      \"inherits\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Windows-only configuration\",\n"
"      \"description\": \"This build is only available on Windows\",\n"
"      \"condition\": {\n"
"        \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"        \"lhs\": \"${hostSystemName}\",\n"
"        \"rhs\": \"Windows\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"buildPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"testPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"output\": {\"outputOnFailure\": true},\n"
"      \"execution\": {\"noTestsAction\": \"error\", \"stopOnFailure\": "
"true}\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"packagePresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"configurePreset\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"generators\": [\n"
"        \"TGZ\"\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"workflowPresets\": [\n"
"    {\n"
"      \"name\": \"default\",\n"
"      \"steps\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"configure\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"build\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"test\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"type\": \"package\",\n"
"          \"name\": \"default\"\n"
"        }\n"
"      ]\n"
"    }\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"vendor\": {\n"
"    \"example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0\": {\n"
"      \"autoFormat\": false\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:42
msgid ""
"Preset files specifying version ``10`` or above may include comments using "
"the key ``$comment`` at any level within the JSON object to provide "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:45
msgid "The root object recognizes the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:49
msgid "``$schema``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:50
msgid ""
"An optional string that provides a URI to the JSON schema that describes the "
"structure of this JSON document. This field is used for validation and "
"autocompletion in editors that support JSON schema. It doesn't affect the "
"behavior of the document itself. If this field is not specified, the JSON "
"document will still be valid, but tools that use JSON schema for validation "
"and autocompletion may not function correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:57
msgid "``version``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:58
msgid ""
"A required integer representing the version of the JSON schema. See "
"`Versions`_ for discussion of the supported versions and the corresponding "
"version of CMake in which they were added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:62
msgid "``cmakeMinimumRequired``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:63
msgid ""
"An optional object representing the minimum version of CMake needed to build "
"this project. This object consists of the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:66
msgid "``major``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:67
msgid "An optional integer representing the major version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:69
msgid "``minor``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:70
msgid "An optional integer representing the minor version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:72
msgid "``patch``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:73
msgid "An optional integer representing the patch version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:75
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:812
msgid "``include``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:76
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing files to include. If the filenames "
"are not absolute, they are considered relative to the current file. This is "
"allowed in preset files specifying version ``4`` or above. See `Includes`_ "
"for discussion of the constraints on included files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:81
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:179
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:482
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:662
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1025
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1148
msgid "``vendor``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:82
msgid ""
"An optional map containing vendor-specific information. CMake does not "
"interpret the contents of this field except to verify that it is a map if it "
"does exist. However, the keys should be a vendor-specific domain name "
"followed by a ``/``-separated path. For example, the Example IDE 1.0 could "
"use ``example.com/ExampleIDE/1.0``. The value of each field can be anything "
"desired by the vendor, though will typically be a map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:89
msgid "``configurePresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:90
msgid ""
"An optional array of `Configure Preset`_ objects. This is allowed in preset "
"files specifying version ``1`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:93
msgid "``buildPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:94
msgid ""
"An optional array of `Build Preset`_ objects. This is allowed in preset "
"files specifying version ``2`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:97
msgid "``testPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:98
msgid ""
"An optional array of `Test Preset`_ objects. This is allowed in preset files "
"specifying version ``2`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:101
msgid "``packagePresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:102
msgid ""
"An optional array of `Package Preset`_ objects. This is allowed in preset "
"files specifying version ``6`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:105
msgid "``workflowPresets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:106
msgid ""
"An optional array of `Workflow Preset`_ objects. This is allowed in preset "
"files specifying version ``6`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:110
msgid "Includes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:112
msgid ""
"``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` can include other files "
"with the ``include`` field in file version ``4`` and later. Files included "
"by these files can also include other files. If ``CMakePresets.json`` and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` are both present, ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` "
"implicitly includes ``CMakePresets.json``, even with no ``include`` field, "
"in all versions of the format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:119
msgid ""
"If a preset file contains presets that inherit from presets in another file, "
"the file must include the other file either directly or indirectly. Include "
"cycles are not allowed among files. If ``a.json`` includes ``b.json``, ``b."
"json`` cannot include ``a.json``. However, a file may be included multiple "
"times from the same file or from different files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:125
msgid ""
"Files directly or indirectly included from ``CMakePresets.json`` should be "
"guaranteed to be provided by the project. ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` may "
"include files from anywhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:129
msgid ""
"Starting from version ``7``, the ``include`` field supports `macro "
"expansion`_, but only ``$penv{}`` macro expansion. Starting from version "
"``9``, other macro expansions are also available, except for ``$env{}`` and "
"preset-specific macros, i.e., those derived from the fields inside a "
"preset's definition like ``presetName``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:136
msgid "Configure Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:138
msgid ""
"Each entry of the ``configurePresets`` array is a JSON object that may "
"contain the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:141
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:444
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:625
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:816
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:855
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:989
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1139
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1170
msgid "``name``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:142
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`cmake --preset` option. There must not be "
"two configure presets in the union of ``CMakePresets.json`` and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same directory with the same name. However, "
"a configure preset may have the same name as a build, test, package, or "
"workflow preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:149
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:453
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:633
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:997
msgid "``hidden``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:150
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not a preset should be hidden. If "
"a preset is hidden, it cannot be used in the :option:`--preset <cmake --"
"preset>` argument, will not show up in the :manual:`CMake GUI <cmake-"
"gui(1)>`, and does not have to have a valid ``generator`` or ``binaryDir``, "
"even from inheritance. ``hidden`` presets are intended to be used as a base "
"for other presets to inherit via the ``inherits`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:158
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:461
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:641
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1005
msgid "``inherits``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:159
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:462
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:642
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1006
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing the names of presets to inherit "
"from. This field can also be a string, which is equivalent to an array "
"containing one string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:163
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:466
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:646
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1010
msgid ""
"The preset will inherit all of the fields from the ``inherits`` presets by "
"default (except ``name``, ``hidden``, ``inherits``, ``description``, and "
"``displayName``), but can override them as desired. If multiple ``inherits`` "
"presets provide conflicting values for the same field, the earlier preset in "
"the ``inherits`` array will be preferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:170
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:473
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:653
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1017
msgid ""
"A preset can only inherit from another preset that is defined in the same "
"file or in one of the files it includes (directly or indirectly). Presets in "
"``CMakePresets.json`` may not inherit from presets in ``CMakeUserPresets."
"json``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:175
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:478
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:658
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1022
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1253
msgid "``condition``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:176
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:479
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:659
msgid ""
"An optional `Condition`_ object. This is allowed in preset files specifying "
"version ``3`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:180
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:483
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:663
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1026
msgid ""
"An optional map containing vendor-specific information. CMake does not "
"interpret the contents of this field except to verify that it is a map if it "
"does exist. However, it should follow the same conventions as the root-level "
"``vendor`` field. If vendors use their own per-preset ``vendor`` field, they "
"should implement inheritance in a sensible manner when appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:187
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:490
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:670
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1033
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1154
msgid "``displayName``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:188
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:491
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:671
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1034
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1155
msgid "An optional string with a human-friendly name of the preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:190
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:493
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:673
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1036
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1157
msgid "``description``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:191
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:494
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:674
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1037
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1158
msgid "An optional string with a human-friendly description of the preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:195
msgid "``generator``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:196
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the :manual:`generator <cmake-"
"generators(7)>` to use for the preset. If ``generator`` is not specified, it "
"must be inherited from the ``inherits`` preset (unless this preset is "
"``hidden``). In version ``3`` or above, this field may be omitted to fall "
"back to regular generator discovery procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:202
msgid ""
"Note that for :ref:`Visual Studio generators`, unlike in the command line :"
"option:`-G <cmake -G>` argument, you cannot include the platform name in the "
"generator name. Use the ``architecture`` field instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:206
msgid "``architecture``, ``toolset``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:207
msgid ""
"Optional fields representing the platform and toolset, respectively, for :"
"manual:`generators <cmake-generators(7)>` that support them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:210
msgid ""
"See :option:`cmake -A` option for possible values for ``architecture`` and :"
"option:`cmake -T` for ``toolset``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:213
msgid "Each may be either a string or an object with the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:215
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:293
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1195
msgid "``value``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:216
msgid "An optional string representing the value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:218
msgid "``strategy``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:219
msgid ""
"An optional string telling CMake how to handle the ``architecture`` or "
"``toolset`` field. Valid values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:222
msgid "``\"set\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:223
msgid ""
"Set the respective value. This will result in an error for generators that "
"do not support the respective field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:226
msgid "``\"external\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:227
msgid ""
"Do not set the value, even if the generator supports it. This is useful if, "
"for example, a preset uses the Ninja generator, and an IDE knows how to set "
"up the Visual C++ environment from the ``architecture`` and ``toolset`` "
"fields. In that case, CMake will ignore the field, but the IDE can use them "
"to set up the environment before invoking CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:234
msgid ""
"If no ``strategy`` field is given, or if the field uses the string form "
"rather than the object form, the behavior is the same as ``\"set\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:239
msgid "``toolchainFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:240
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the path to the toolchain file. This field "
"supports `macro expansion`_. If a relative path is specified, it is "
"calculated relative to the build directory, and if not found, relative to "
"the source directory. This field takes precedence over any :variable:"
"`CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE` value. It is allowed in preset files specifying "
"version ``3`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:249
msgid "``graphviz``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:250
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the path to the graphviz input file, that "
"will contain all the library and executable dependencies in the project.  "
"See the documentation for :option:`cmake --graphviz` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:255
msgid ""
"This field supports `macro expansion`_. If a relative path is specified, it "
"is calculated relative to the current working directory. It is allowed in "
"preset files specifying version ``10`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:261
msgid "``binaryDir``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:262
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the path to the output binary directory. "
"This field supports `macro expansion`_. If a relative path is specified, it "
"is calculated relative to the source directory. If ``binaryDir`` is not "
"specified, it must be inherited from the ``inherits`` preset (unless this "
"preset is ``hidden``). In version ``3`` or above, this field may be omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:271
msgid "``installDir``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:272
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the path to the installation directory, "
"which will be used as the :variable:`CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` variable. This "
"field supports `macro expansion`_. If a relative path is specified, it is "
"calculated relative to the source directory. This is allowed in preset files "
"specifying version ``3`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:278
msgid "``cmakeExecutable``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:279
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the path to the CMake executable to use for "
"this preset. This is reserved for use by IDEs, and is not used by CMake "
"itself. IDEs that use this field should expand any macros in it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:283
msgid "``cacheVariables``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:284
msgid ""
"An optional map of cache variables. The key is the variable name (which may "
"not be an empty string), and the value is either ``null``, a boolean (which "
"is equivalent to a value of ``\"TRUE\"`` or ``\"FALSE\"`` and a type of "
"``BOOL``), a string representing the value of the variable (which supports "
"`macro expansion`_), or an object with the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:290
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1166
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1187
msgid "``type``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:291
msgid "An optional string representing the type of the variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:294
msgid ""
"A required string or boolean representing the value of the variable. A "
"boolean is equivalent to ``\"TRUE\"`` or ``\"FALSE\"``. This field supports "
"`macro expansion`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:298
msgid ""
"Cache variables are inherited through the ``inherits`` field, and the "
"preset's variables will be the union of its own ``cacheVariables`` and the "
"``cacheVariables`` from all its parents. If multiple presets in this union "
"define the same variable, the standard rules of ``inherits`` are applied. "
"Setting a variable to ``null`` causes it to not be set, even if a value was "
"inherited from another preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:305
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:498
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:676
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1039
msgid "``environment``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:306
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:499
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:677
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1040
msgid ""
"An optional map of environment variables. The key is the variable name "
"(which may not be an empty string), and the value is either ``null`` or a "
"string representing the value of the variable. Each variable is set "
"regardless of whether or not a value was given to it by the process's "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:312
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:505
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:683
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1046
msgid ""
"This field supports `macro expansion`_, and environment variables in this "
"map may reference each other, and may be listed in any order, as long as "
"such references do not cause a cycle (for example, if ``ENV_1`` is "
"``$env{ENV_2}``, ``ENV_2`` may not be ``$env{ENV_1}``).  ``$penv{NAME}`` "
"allows one to prepend or append values to existing environment variables by "
"accessing only values from the parent environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:319
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:512
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:690
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1053
msgid ""
"Environment variables are inherited through the ``inherits`` field, and the "
"preset's environment will be the union of its own ``environment`` and the "
"``environment`` from all its parents. If multiple presets in this union "
"define the same variable, the standard rules of ``inherits`` are applied. "
"Setting a variable to ``null`` causes it to not be set, even if a value was "
"inherited from another preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:326
msgid "``warnings``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:327
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying the warnings to enable. The object may contain "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:330
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:361
msgid "``dev``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:331
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Equivalent to passing :option:`-Wdev <cmake -Wdev>` or :"
"option:`-Wno-dev <cmake -Wno-dev>` on the command line. This may not be set "
"to ``false`` if ``errors.dev`` is set to ``true``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:335
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:366
msgid "``deprecated``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:336
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Equivalent to passing :option:`-Wdeprecated <cmake -"
"Wdeprecated>` or :option:`-Wno-deprecated <cmake -Wno-deprecated>` on the "
"command line. This may not be set to ``false`` if ``errors.deprecated`` is "
"set to ``true``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:342
msgid "``uninitialized``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:343
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``true`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--warn-uninitialized <cmake --warn-uninitialized>` on the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:347
msgid "``unusedCli``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:348
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``false`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--no-warn-unused-cli <cmake --no-warn-unused-cli>` on the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:352
msgid "``systemVars``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:353
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``true`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--check-system-vars <cmake --check-system-vars>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:357
msgid "``errors``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:358
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying the errors to enable. The object may contain "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:362
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Equivalent to passing :option:`-Werror=dev <cmake -"
"Werror>` or :option:`-Wno-error=dev <cmake -Werror>` on the command line. "
"This may not be set to ``true`` if ``warnings.dev`` is set to ``false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:367
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Equivalent to passing :option:`-Werror=deprecated "
"<cmake -Werror>` or :option:`-Wno-error=deprecated <cmake -Werror>` on the "
"command line. This may not be set to ``true`` if ``warnings.deprecated`` is "
"set to ``false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:373
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:746
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1092
msgid "``debug``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:374
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying debug options. The object may contain the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:377
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:723
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1089
msgid "``output``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:378
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``true`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--debug-output <cmake --debug-output>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:381
msgid "``tryCompile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:382
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``true`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--debug-trycompile <cmake --debug-trycompile>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:386
msgid "``find``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:387
msgid ""
"An optional boolean. Setting this to ``true`` is equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--debug-find <cmake --debug-find>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:392
msgid "``trace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:393
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying trace options. This is allowed in preset files "
"specifying version ``7``. The object may contain the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:396
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:939
msgid "``mode``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:397
msgid "An optional string that specifies the trace mode. Valid values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:399
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:586
msgid "``on``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:400
msgid ""
"Causes a trace of all calls made and from where to be printed. Equivalent to "
"passing :option:`--trace <cmake --trace>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:404
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:589
msgid "``off``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:405
msgid "A trace of all calls will not be printed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:407
msgid "``expand``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:408
msgid ""
"Causes a trace with variables expanded of all calls made and from where to "
"be printed. Equivalent to passing :option:`--trace-expand <cmake --trace-"
"expand>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:412
msgid "``format``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:413
msgid ""
"An optional string that specifies the format output of the trace. Valid "
"values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:416
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:930
msgid "``human``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:417
msgid ""
"Prints each trace line in a human-readable format. This is the default "
"format.  Equivalent to passing :option:`--trace-format=human <cmake --trace-"
"format>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:422
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:932
msgid "``json-v1``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:423
msgid ""
"Prints each line as a separate JSON document.  Equivalent to passing :option:"
"`--trace-format=json-v1 <cmake --trace-format>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:427
msgid "``source``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:428
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing the paths of source files to be "
"traced.  This field can also be a string, which is equivalent to an array "
"containing one string.  Equivalent to passing :option:`--trace-source <cmake "
"--trace-source>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:433
msgid "``redirect``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:434
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a path to a trace output file.  Equivalent to "
"passing :option:`--trace-redirect <cmake --trace-redirect>` on the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:439
msgid "Build Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:441
msgid ""
"Each entry of the ``buildPresets`` array is a JSON object that may contain "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:445
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`cmake --build --preset <cmake--build --"
"preset>` option. There must not be two build presets in the union of "
"``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same directory "
"with the same name. However, a build preset may have the same name as a "
"configure, test, package, or workflow preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:454
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not a preset should be hidden. If "
"a preset is hidden, it cannot be used in the :option:`--preset <cmake--build "
"--preset>` argument and does not have to have a valid ``configurePreset``, "
"even from inheritance. ``hidden`` presets are intended to be used as a base "
"for other presets to inherit via the ``inherits`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:521
msgid ""
"For a CMake project using :module:`ExternalProject` with a configuration "
"preset having environment variables needed in the ExternalProject, use a "
"build preset that inherits that configuration preset or the ExternalProject "
"will not have the environment variables set in the configuration preset. "
"Example: suppose the host defaults to one compiler (say Clang) and the user "
"wishes to use another compiler (say GCC). Set configuration preset "
"environment variables :envvar:`CC` and :envvar:`CXX` and use a build preset "
"that inherits that configuration preset. Otherwise the ExternalProject may "
"use a different (system default) compiler than the top-level CMake project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:532
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:697
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1060
msgid "``configurePreset``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:533
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying the name of a configure preset to associate "
"with this build preset. If ``configurePreset`` is not specified, it must be "
"inherited from the inherits preset (unless this preset is hidden). The build "
"directory is inferred from the configure preset, so the build will take "
"place in the same ``binaryDir`` that the configuration did."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:540
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:705
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1068
msgid "``inheritConfigureEnvironment``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:541
msgid ""
"An optional boolean that defaults to true. If true, the environment "
"variables from the associated configure preset are inherited after all "
"inherited build preset environments, but before environment variables "
"explicitly specified in this build preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:548
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:902
msgid "``jobs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:549
msgid ""
"An optional integer. Equivalent to passing :option:`--parallel <cmake--build "
"--parallel>` or ``-j`` on the command line. If the value is ``0``, it is "
"equivalent to passing ``--parallel`` with ``<jobs>`` omitted; alternatively, "
"one can define the environment variable :envvar:`CMAKE_BUILD_PARALLEL_LEVEL` "
"as an empty string using the ``environment`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:558
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:913
msgid ""
"This field does not accept negative integer values, regardless of the "
"version in the preset file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:561
msgid "``targets``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:562
msgid ""
"An optional string or array of strings. Equivalent to passing :option:`--"
"target <cmake--build --target>` or ``-t`` on the command line. Vendors may "
"ignore the targets property or hide build presets that explicitly specify "
"targets. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:567
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:711
msgid "``configuration``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:568
msgid ""
"An optional string. Equivalent to passing :option:`--config <cmake--build --"
"config>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:571
msgid "``cleanFirst``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:572
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--clean-first "
"<cmake--build --clean-first>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:577
msgid "``resolvePackageReferences``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:578
msgid ""
"An optional string that specifies the package resolve mode. This is allowed "
"in preset files specifying version ``4`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:581
msgid ""
"Package references are used to define dependencies to packages from external "
"package managers. Currently only NuGet in combination with the :ref:`Visual "
"Studio generators` is supported. If there are no targets that define package "
"references, this option does nothing. Valid values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:587
msgid "Causes package references to be resolved before attempting a build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:590
msgid ""
"Package references will not be resolved. Note that this may cause errors in "
"some build environments, such as .NET SDK style projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:593
msgid "``only``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:594
msgid "Only resolve package references, but do not perform a build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:598
msgid ""
"The command line parameter :option:`--resolve-package-references <cmake--"
"build --resolve-package-references>` will take priority over this setting. "
"If the command line parameter is not provided and this setting is not "
"specified, an environment-specific cache variable will be evaluated to "
"decide, if package restoration should be performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:605
msgid ""
"When using the :ref:`Visual Studio generators`, package references are "
"defined using the :prop_tgt:`VS_PACKAGE_REFERENCES` property. Package "
"references are restored using NuGet. It can be disabled by setting the :"
"variable:`CMAKE_VS_NUGET_PACKAGE_RESTORE` variable to ``OFF``. This can also "
"be done from within a configure preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:611
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:738
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1097
msgid "``verbose``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:612
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--verbose <cmake--"
"build --verbose>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:615
msgid "``nativeToolOptions``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:616
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings. Equivalent to passing options after ``--`` on "
"the command line. The array values support macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:620
msgid "Test Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:622
msgid ""
"Each entry of the ``testPresets`` array is a JSON object that may contain "
"the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:626
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`ctest --preset` option. There must not be "
"two test presets in the union of ``CMakePresets.json`` and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same directory with the same name. However, "
"a test preset may have the same name as a configure, build, package, or "
"workflow preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:634
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not a preset should be hidden. If "
"a preset is hidden, it cannot be used in the :option:`--preset <ctest --"
"preset>` argument and does not have to have a valid ``configurePreset``, "
"even from inheritance. ``hidden`` presets are intended to be used as a base "
"for other presets to inherit via the ``inherits`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:698
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying the name of a configure preset to associate "
"with this test preset. If ``configurePreset`` is not specified, it must be "
"inherited from the inherits preset (unless this preset is hidden). The build "
"directory is inferred from the configure preset, so tests will run in the "
"same ``binaryDir`` that the configuration did and build did."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:706
msgid ""
"An optional boolean that defaults to true. If true, the environment "
"variables from the associated configure preset are inherited after all "
"inherited test preset environments, but before environment variables "
"explicitly specified in this test preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:712
msgid ""
"An optional string. Equivalent to passing :option:`--build-config <ctest --"
"build-config>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:715
msgid "``overwriteConfigurationFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:716
msgid ""
"An optional array of configuration options to overwrite options specified in "
"the CTest configuration file. Equivalent to passing :option:`--overwrite "
"<ctest --overwrite>` for each value in the array. The array values support "
"macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:724
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying output options. The object may contain the "
"following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:727
msgid "``shortProgress``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:728
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--progress <ctest "
"--progress>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:731
msgid "``verbosity``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:732
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying verbosity level. Must be one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:735
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:971
msgid "``default``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:736
msgid "Equivalent to passing no verbosity flags on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:739
msgid ""
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--verbose <ctest --verbose>` on the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:742
msgid "``extra``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:743
msgid ""
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--extra-verbose <ctest --extra-verbose>` on "
"the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:747
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--debug <ctest --"
"debug>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:750
msgid "``outputOnFailure``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:751
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--output-on-"
"failure <ctest --output-on-failure>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:755
msgid "``quiet``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:756
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--quiet <ctest --"
"quiet>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:759
msgid "``outputLogFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:760
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a path to a log file. Equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--output-log <ctest --output-log>` on the command line. This field "
"supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:766
msgid "``outputJUnitFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:767
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a path to a JUnit file. Equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--output-junit <ctest --output-junit>` on the command line. This "
"field supports macro expansion. This is allowed in preset files specifying "
"version ``6`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:772
msgid "``labelSummary``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:773
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If false, equivalent to passing :option:`--no-label-"
"summary <ctest --no-label-summary>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:777
msgid "``subprojectSummary``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:778
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If false, equivalent to passing :option:`--no-subproject-"
"summary <ctest --no-subproject-summary>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:782
msgid "``maxPassedTestOutputSize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:783
msgid ""
"An optional integer specifying the maximum output for passed tests in bytes. "
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--test-output-size-passed <ctest --test-"
"output-size-passed>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:788
msgid "``maxFailedTestOutputSize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:789
msgid ""
"An optional integer specifying the maximum output for failed tests in bytes. "
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--test-output-size-failed <ctest --test-"
"output-size-failed>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:796
msgid "``testOutputTruncation``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:797
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying the test output truncation mode. Equivalent to "
"passing :option:`--test-output-truncation <ctest --test-output-truncation>` "
"on the command line. This is allowed in preset files specifying version "
"``5`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:803
msgid "``maxTestNameWidth``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:804
msgid ""
"An optional integer specifying the maximum width of a test name to output. "
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--max-width <ctest --max-width>` on the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:808
msgid "``filter``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:809
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying how to filter the tests to run. The object may "
"contain the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:813
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying which tests to include. The object may contain "
"the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:817
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for test names. Equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--tests-regex <ctest --tests-regex>` on the command line. This field "
"supports macro expansion. CMake regex syntax is described under :ref:"
"`string(REGEX) <Regex Specification>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:822
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:860
msgid "``label``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:823
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for test labels. Equivalent to "
"passing :option:`--label-regex <ctest --label-regex>` on the command line. "
"This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:827
msgid "``useUnion``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:828
msgid ""
"An optional bool. Equivalent to passing :option:`--union <ctest --union>` on "
"the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:831
msgid "``index``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:832
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying tests to include by test index. The object may "
"contain the following fields. Can also be an optional string specifying a "
"file with the command line syntax for :option:`--tests-information <ctest --"
"tests-information>`. If specified as a string, this field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:838
msgid "``start``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:839
msgid "An optional integer specifying a test index to start testing at."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:841
msgid "``end``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:842
msgid "An optional integer specifying a test index to stop testing at."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:844
msgid "``stride``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:845
msgid "An optional integer specifying the increment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:847
msgid "``specificTests``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:848
msgid "An optional array of integers specifying specific test indices to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:851
msgid "``exclude``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:852
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying which tests to exclude. The object may contain "
"the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:856
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for test names. Equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--exclude-regex <ctest --exclude-regex>` on the command line. This "
"field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:861
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for test labels. Equivalent to "
"passing :option:`--label-exclude <ctest --label-exclude>` on the command "
"line. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:865
msgid "``fixtures``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:866
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying which fixtures to exclude from adding tests. "
"The object may contain the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:869
msgid "``any``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:870
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for text fixtures to exclude from "
"adding any tests. Equivalent to :option:`--fixture-exclude-any <ctest --"
"fixture-exclude-any>` on the command line. This field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:875
msgid "``setup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:876
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for text fixtures to exclude from "
"adding setup tests. Equivalent to :option:`--fixture-exclude-setup <ctest --"
"fixture-exclude-setup>` on the command line. This field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:881
msgid "``cleanup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:882
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying a regex for text fixtures to exclude from "
"adding cleanup tests. Equivalent to :option:`--fixture-exclude-cleanup "
"<ctest --fixture-exclude-cleanup>` on the command line. This field supports "
"macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:887
msgid "``execution``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:888
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying options for test execution. The object may "
"contain the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:891
msgid "``stopOnFailure``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:892
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--stop-on-failure "
"<ctest --stop-on-failure>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:896
msgid "``enableFailover``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:897
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`-F <ctest -F>` on "
"the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:903
msgid ""
"An optional integer. Equivalent to passing :option:`--parallel <ctest --"
"parallel>` on the command line. If the value is ``0``, it is equivalent to "
"unbounded parallelism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:907
msgid ""
"In preset files specifying version ``11`` or above, this field can also be a "
"string, in which case it must be empty, and is equivalent to passing ``--"
"parallel`` with ``<jobs>`` omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:916
msgid "``resourceSpecFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:917
msgid ""
"An optional string. Equivalent to passing :option:`--resource-spec-file "
"<ctest --resource-spec-file>` on the command line. This field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:921
msgid "``testLoad``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:922
msgid ""
"An optional integer. Equivalent to passing :option:`--test-load <ctest --"
"test-load>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:925
msgid "``showOnly``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:926
msgid ""
"An optional string. Equivalent to passing :option:`--show-only <ctest --show-"
"only>` on the command line. The string must be one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:934
msgid "``repeat``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:935
msgid ""
"An optional object specifying how to repeat tests. Equivalent to passing :"
"option:`--repeat <ctest --repeat>` on the command line. The object must have "
"the following fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:940
msgid "A required string. Must be one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:942
msgid "``until-fail``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:944
msgid "``until-pass``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:946
msgid "``after-timeout``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:948
msgid "``count``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:949
msgid "A required integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:951
msgid "``interactiveDebugging``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:952
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--interactive-"
"debug-mode 1 <ctest --interactive-debug-mode>` on the command line. If "
"false, equivalent to passing :option:`--interactive-debug-mode 0 <ctest --"
"interactive-debug-mode>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:958
msgid "``scheduleRandom``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:959
msgid ""
"An optional bool. If true, equivalent to passing :option:`--schedule-random "
"<ctest --schedule-random>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:963
msgid "``timeout``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:964
msgid ""
"An optional integer. Equivalent to passing :option:`--timeout <ctest --"
"timeout>` on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:967
msgid "``noTestsAction``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:968
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying the behavior if no tests are found. Must be "
"one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:972
msgid "Equivalent to not passing any value on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:974
msgid "``error``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:975
msgid ""
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--no-tests=error <ctest --no-tests>` on the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:978
msgid "``ignore``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:979
msgid ""
"Equivalent to passing :option:`--no-tests=ignore <ctest --no-tests>` on the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:983
msgid "Package Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:985
msgid ""
"Package presets may be used in schema version ``6`` or above. Each entry of "
"the ``packagePresets`` array is a JSON object that may contain the following "
"fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:990
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`cpack --preset` option. There must not be "
"two package presets in the union of ``CMakePresets.json`` and "
"``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same directory with the same name. However, "
"a package preset may have the same name as a configure, build, test, or "
"workflow preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:998
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not a preset should be hidden. If "
"a preset is hidden, it cannot be used in the :option:`--preset <cpack --"
"preset>` argument and does not have to have a valid ``configurePreset``, "
"even from inheritance. ``hidden`` presets are intended to be used as a base "
"for other presets to inherit via the ``inherits`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1023
msgid "An optional `Condition`_ object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1061
msgid ""
"An optional string specifying the name of a configure preset to associate "
"with this package preset. If ``configurePreset`` is not specified, it must "
"be inherited from the inherits preset (unless this preset is hidden). The "
"build directory is inferred from the configure preset, so packaging will run "
"in the same ``binaryDir`` that the configuration did and build did."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1069
msgid ""
"An optional boolean that defaults to true. If true, the environment "
"variables from the associated configure preset are inherited after all "
"inherited package preset environments, but before environment variables "
"explicitly specified in this package preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1074
msgid "``generators``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1075
msgid "An optional array of strings representing generators for CPack to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1077
msgid "``configurations``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1078
msgid ""
"An optional array of strings representing build configurations for CPack to "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1081
msgid "``variables``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1082
msgid ""
"An optional map of variables to pass to CPack, equivalent to :option:`-D "
"<cpack -D>` arguments. Each key is the name of a variable, and the value is "
"the string to assign to that variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1086
msgid "``configFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1087
msgid "An optional string representing the config file for CPack to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1090
msgid "An optional object specifying output options. Valid keys are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1093
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not to print debug information. A "
"value of ``true`` is equivalent to passing :option:`--debug <cpack --debug>` "
"on the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1098
msgid ""
"An optional boolean specifying whether or not to print verbosely. A value of "
"``true`` is equivalent to passing :option:`--verbose <cpack --verbose>` on "
"the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1102
msgid "``packageName``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1103
msgid "An optional string representing the package name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1107
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1118
msgid ""
"Due to problems with the implementation, this field does not affect the name "
"of the final package file produced.  Other aspects of the package may use "
"the value though, leading to inconsistencies. A future CMake release may "
"address this problem, but until then, it is recommended that this field not "
"be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1113
msgid "``packageVersion``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1114
msgid "An optional string representing the package version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1124
msgid "``packageDirectory``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1125
msgid ""
"An optional string representing the directory in which to place the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1127
msgid "``vendorName``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1128
msgid "An optional string representing the vendor name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1133
msgid "Workflow Preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1135
msgid ""
"Workflow presets may be used in schema version ``6`` or above. Each entry of "
"the ``workflowPresets`` array is a JSON object that may contain the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1140
msgid ""
"A required string representing the machine-friendly name of the preset. This "
"identifier is used in the :option:`cmake --workflow --preset <cmake--"
"workflow --preset>` option. There must not be two workflow presets in the "
"union of ``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` in the same "
"directory with the same name. However, a workflow preset may have the same "
"name as a configure, build, test, or package preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1149
msgid ""
"An optional map containing vendor-specific information. CMake does not "
"interpret the contents of this field except to verify that it is a map if it "
"does exist. However, it should follow the same conventions as the root-level "
"``vendor`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1160
msgid "``steps``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1161
msgid ""
"A required array of objects describing the steps of the workflow. The first "
"step must be a configure preset, and all subsequent steps must be non-"
"configure presets whose ``configurePreset`` field matches the starting "
"configure preset. Each object may contain the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1167
msgid ""
"A required string. The first step must be ``configure``. Subsequent steps "
"must be either ``build``, ``test``, or ``package``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1171
msgid ""
"A required string representing the name of the configure, build, test, or "
"package preset to run as this workflow step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1175
msgid "Condition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1177
msgid ""
"The ``condition`` field of a preset, allowed in preset files specifying "
"version ``3`` or above, is used to determine whether or not the preset is "
"enabled. For example, this can be used to disable a preset on platforms "
"other than Windows. ``condition`` may be either a boolean, ``null``, or an "
"object. If it is a boolean, the boolean indicates whether the preset is "
"enabled or disabled. If it is ``null``, the preset is enabled, but the "
"``null`` condition is not inherited by any presets that may inherit from the "
"preset. Sub-conditions (for example in a ``not``, ``anyOf``, or ``allOf`` "
"condition) may not be ``null``. If it is an object, it has the following "
"fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1188
msgid "A required string with one of the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1190
msgid "``\"const\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1191
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is constant. This is equivalent to using a "
"boolean in place of the object. The condition object will have the following "
"additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1196
msgid ""
"A required boolean which provides a constant value for the condition's "
"evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1199
msgid "``\"equals\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1201
msgid "``\"notEquals\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1202
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition compares two strings to see if they are equal "
"(or not equal). The condition object will have the following additional "
"fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1206
msgid "``lhs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1207
msgid "First string to compare. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1209
msgid "``rhs``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1210
msgid "Second string to compare. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1212
msgid "``\"inList\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1214
msgid "``\"notInList\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1215
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition searches for a string in a list of strings. The "
"condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1218
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1231
msgid "``string``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1219
msgid "A required string to search for. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1221
msgid "``list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1222
msgid ""
"A required array of strings to search. This field supports macro expansion, "
"and uses short-circuit evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1225
msgid "``\"matches\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1227
msgid "``\"notMatches\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1228
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition searches for a regular expression in a string. "
"The condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1232
msgid "A required string to search. This field supports macro expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1234
msgid "``regex``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1235
msgid ""
"A required regular expression to search for. This field supports macro "
"expansion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1238
msgid "``\"anyOf\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1240
msgid "``\"allOf\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1242
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is an aggregation of zero or more nested "
"conditions. The condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1245
msgid "``conditions``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1246
msgid ""
"A required array of condition objects. These conditions use short-circuit "
"evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1249
msgid "``\"not\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1250
msgid ""
"Indicates that the condition is an inversion of another condition. The "
"condition object will have the following additional fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1254
msgid "A required condition object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1257
msgid "Macro Expansion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1259
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, some fields support macro expansion. Macros are "
"recognized in the form ``$<macro-namespace>{<macro-name>}``. All macros are "
"evaluated in the context of the preset being used, even if the macro is in a "
"field that was inherited from another preset. For example, if the ``Base`` "
"preset sets variable ``PRESET_NAME`` to ``${presetName}``, and the "
"``Derived`` preset inherits from ``Base``, ``PRESET_NAME`` will be set to "
"``Derived``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1267
msgid ""
"It is an error to not put a closing brace at the end of a macro name. For "
"example, ``${sourceDir`` is invalid. A dollar sign (``$``) followed by "
"anything other than a left curly brace (``{``) with a possible namespace is "
"interpreted as a literal dollar sign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1272
msgid "Recognized macros include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1274
msgid "``${sourceDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1275
msgid ""
"Path to the project source directory (i.e. the same as :variable:"
"`CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1278
msgid "``${sourceParentDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1279
msgid "Path to the project source directory's parent directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1281
msgid "``${sourceDirName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1282
msgid ""
"The last filename component of ``${sourceDir}``. For example, if "
"``${sourceDir}`` is ``/path/to/source``, this would be ``source``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1285
msgid "``${presetName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1286
msgid "Name specified in the preset's ``name`` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1288
#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1295
msgid "This is a preset-specific macro."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1290
msgid "``${generator}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1291
msgid ""
"Generator specified in the preset's ``generator`` field. For build and test "
"presets, this will evaluate to the generator specified by "
"``configurePreset``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1299
msgid "``${hostSystemName}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1300
msgid ""
"The name of the host operating system. Contains the same value as :variable:"
"`CMAKE_HOST_SYSTEM_NAME`. This is allowed in preset files specifying version "
"``3`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1306
msgid "``${fileDir}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1307
msgid ""
"Path to the directory containing the preset file which contains the macro. "
"This is allowed in preset files specifying version ``4`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1310
msgid "``${dollar}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1311
msgid "A literal dollar sign (``$``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1315
msgid "``${pathListSep}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1316
msgid "Native character for separating lists of paths, such as ``:`` or ``;``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1318
msgid ""
"For example, by setting ``PATH`` to ``/path/to/ninja/"
"bin${pathListSep}$env{PATH}``, ``${pathListSep}`` will expand to the "
"underlying operating system's character used for concatenation in ``PATH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1323
msgid "This is allowed in preset files specifying version ``5`` or above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1325
msgid "``$env{<variable-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1326
msgid ""
"Environment variable with name ``<variable-name>``. The variable name may "
"not be an empty string. If the variable is defined in the ``environment`` "
"field, that value is used instead of the value from the parent environment. "
"If the environment variable is not defined, this evaluates as an empty "
"string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1332
msgid ""
"Note that while Windows environment variable names are case-insensitive, "
"variable names within a preset are still case-sensitive. This may lead to "
"unexpected results when using inconsistent casing. For best results, keep "
"the casing of environment variable names consistent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1337
msgid "``$penv{<variable-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1338
msgid ""
"Similar to ``$env{<variable-name>}``, except that the value only comes from "
"the parent environment, and never from the ``environment`` field. This "
"allows one to prepend or append values to existing environment variables. "
"For example, setting ``PATH`` to ``/path/to/ninja/bin:$penv{PATH}`` will "
"prepend ``/path/to/ninja/bin`` to the ``PATH`` environment variable. This is "
"needed because ``$env{<variable-name>}`` does not allow circular references."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1346
msgid "``$vendor{<macro-name>}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1347
msgid ""
"An extension point for vendors to insert their own macros. CMake will not be "
"able to use presets which have a ``$vendor{<macro-name>}`` macro, and "
"effectively ignores such presets. However, it will still be able to use "
"other presets from the same file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1352
msgid ""
"CMake does not make any attempt to interpret ``$vendor{<macro-name>}`` "
"macros. However, to avoid name collisions, IDE vendors should prefix "
"``<macro-name>`` with a very short (preferably <= 4 characters) vendor "
"identifier prefix, followed by a ``.``, followed by the macro name. For "
"example, the Example IDE could have ``$vendor{xide.ideInstallDir}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1359
msgid "Versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/cmake-presets.7.rst:1361
msgid ""
"The JSON schema of ``CMakePresets.json`` and ``CMakeUserPresets.json`` "
"follows a version scheme where new versions are added and allowed in newer "
"versions of CMake."
msgstr ""

